name: InstantiationError
comment:
Thrown when an application tries to use the Java new construct to instantiate an abstract class or an interface.

Normally, this error is caught by the compiler; this error can only occur at run time if the definition of a class has incompatibly changed.

constructors.name: InstantiationError
constructors.comment: Constructs an InstantiationError with no detail message.

constructors.name: InstantiationError
constructors.comment: Constructs an InstantiationError with the specified detail message.
